{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17599275","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17599275"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:51:20+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:51:20+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15535"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15535","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15535"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.66,0.22,0.03,0.03,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8226"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61767"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8226","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8226"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15535"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47213"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4911"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"7010"},{"type":"tags","id":"7178"},{"type":"tags","id":"9878"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19892"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19895"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61767","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/61767"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe adrenal (suprarenal) medulla contains chromaffin cells that produce and secrete catecholamines.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the neural control of the adrenal medulla?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Postganglionic sympathetic fibres stimulate chromaffin cells","Preganglionic sympathetic fibres stimulate chromaffin cells","Postganglionic parasympathetic fibres inhibit chromaffin cells","Preganglionic parasympathetic fibres stimulate chromaffin cells","Postganglionic sympathetic fibres inhibit chromaffin cells"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe adrenal medulla is innervated by \u003Cstrong\u003Epreganglionic sympathetic fibres\u003C/strong\u003E that originate in the thoracic spinal cord. These fibres travel through the greater splanchnic nerve to synapse directly with chromaffin cells, which are modified postganglionic neurons. This arrangement is unique because typically, \u003Cstrong\u003Epostganglionic sympathetic fibres\u003C/strong\u003E would innervate target tissues.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPostganglionic parasympathetic fibres\u003C/strong\u003E do not innervate the adrenal medulla. Similarly, \u003Cstrong\u003Epreganglionic parasympathetic fibres\u003C/strong\u003E have no role in adrenal medulla control. The suggestion that \u003Cstrong\u003Epostganglionic sympathetic fibres inhibit\u003C/strong\u003E chromaffin cells is incorrect - the system works through stimulation, not inhibition.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Preganglionic sympathetic nerve fibers synapse with chromaffin cells in the adrenal medulla to stimulate catecholamine release","The adrenal medulla is functionally similar to a sympathetic ganglion where chromaffin cells are modified postganglionic neurons"],"references":["Lotfi CFP, Kremer JL, Dos Santos Passaia B, Cavalcante IP. The human adrenal cortex: growth control and disorders. Clinics (Sao Paulo). 2018 Sep 6;73(suppl 1):e473s. doi: 10.6061/clinics/2018/e473s. PMID: 30208164; PMCID: PMC6113920","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47213"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15535"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47213","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/47213"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-16T13:21:10+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-16T13:21:44+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8226"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61767"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4911","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4911"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Autonomic nervous system","synonyms":